WEBVTT

00:02.535 --> 00:04.753
♪ My name is Cleveland Brown

00:04.755 --> 00:07.021
♪ And I am proud to be

00:07.023 --> 00:09.375
♪ Right back
In my hometown ♪

00:09.377 --> 00:11.793
♪ With my new family

00:11.795 --> 00:14.012
♪ There's old friends
And new friends ♪

00:14.014 --> 00:16.414
♪ And even a bear

00:16.416 --> 00:18.616
♪ Through good times
And bad times ♪

00:18.618 --> 00:20.218
♪ It's true love we share ♪

00:20.220 --> 00:22.354
♪ And so I found a place

00:22.356 --> 00:24.590
♪ Where everyone will know

00:24.592 --> 00:26.959
♪ My happy mustache face

00:26.961 --> 00:29.027
♪ This is <i>The Cleveland Show</i> ♪

00:29.029 --> 00:31.129
[LAUGHS]

00:31.131 --> 00:33.865
[♪]

00:34.850 --> 00:36.652
Good morning, family.

00:36.654 --> 00:37.852
Good morning, baby.

00:37.854 --> 00:38.887
How'd you sleep?

00:38.889 --> 00:41.490
Oh, this?
I'm glad you asked.

00:41.492 --> 00:44.142
This is my magnus opus.

00:44.144 --> 00:45.494
<i>Waderman.</i>

00:45.496 --> 00:46.628
A comic book?

00:46.630 --> 00:48.997
Cleveland, hush.
Sit down and eat your eggs.

00:48.999 --> 00:53.469
Shame the fool who hath time
for eateth eggs of scramble,

00:53.471 --> 00:57.473
as our breathing hours
are so few and so precious.

00:57.475 --> 00:58.657
What are you talking about?

00:58.659 --> 01:00.058
Donna, all my life,

01:00.060 --> 01:01.894
I've deferred my dreams.

01:01.896 --> 01:03.729
You said I was your dream.

01:03.731 --> 01:06.197
Yeah, and I deferred
you 25 years.

01:06.199 --> 01:08.233
I'm talking about
my other dream,

01:08.235 --> 01:12.270
to write, color
and staple my own comic book,

01:12.272 --> 01:14.472
and last night I finished it.

01:14.474 --> 01:16.542
It's called <i>Waderman.</i>

01:16.544 --> 01:17.743
What's a wader?

01:17.745 --> 01:20.846
What's a wader?
Go fly-fishing much?

01:20.848 --> 01:22.614
They're thigh-high rubber boots

01:22.616 --> 01:25.316
that keep your pants dry
in shallow water.

01:25.318 --> 01:26.985
I first had the idea

01:26.987 --> 01:29.587
one fateful day back
in high school.

01:29.589 --> 01:31.957
[♪]

01:40.633 --> 01:43.519
Oh, I wish I had
the perfect opportunity,

01:43.521 --> 01:47.656
to show Donna Tubbs
I'm the one for her.

01:51.327 --> 01:52.978
Hey, Cleveland. Agh!

01:52.980 --> 01:55.213
My wish came true!

01:55.215 --> 01:57.416
But I just bought these shoes.

01:57.418 --> 02:00.685
I know, I'll take them off
and then go in. Okay.

02:00.687 --> 02:01.853
[GRUNTING]

02:01.855 --> 02:04.123
DONNA:
Help! Help!
Someone help me!

02:04.125 --> 02:07.092
But my socks.
I'll remove those as well.

02:07.094 --> 02:09.661
DONNA:
Anyone! I'll marry anyone
who helps me.

02:09.663 --> 02:11.196
Hm. No towel.
[DONNA SCREAMING]

02:11.198 --> 02:14.333
Guess I'll just wait for my feet
to dry when I get out.

02:14.335 --> 02:17.136
Watch my red Keds?
No. Not my problem.

02:17.138 --> 02:19.338
[DONNA CONTINUES SCREAMING]

02:20.723 --> 02:21.923
DONNA:
Help!

02:24.293 --> 02:27.028
You weigh more
than I thought you would.

02:27.030 --> 02:29.664
My hero.

02:32.201 --> 02:34.502
Hey. Your Keds are
in the fountain.

02:34.504 --> 02:36.170
My red Keds!

02:36.172 --> 02:40.041
That night I swore that I would
never again let shallow water

02:40.043 --> 02:42.644
stand in the way
of what ought to be.

02:42.646 --> 02:45.647
And so Waderman was born.

02:45.649 --> 02:48.350
Which is why
for our summer vacation,

02:48.352 --> 02:51.420
we're going to debut <i>Waderman,</i>

02:51.422 --> 02:55.490
at this year's Comic-Con
in San Diego.

02:55.492 --> 02:57.709
[♪]

02:57.711 --> 03:00.395
No way.

03:00.397 --> 03:01.779
Cleveland, I don't think

03:01.781 --> 03:03.781
that sounds like much
of a vacation.

03:03.783 --> 03:06.385
That's because you don't know
what Comic-Con is.

03:06.387 --> 03:08.103
Imagine a hundred thousand

03:08.105 --> 03:10.405
unwashed comic book fans
in costume,

03:10.407 --> 03:12.774
shoehorned into
a musky convention center,

03:12.776 --> 03:15.076
that smells like
ass and corn chips,

03:15.078 --> 03:17.946
all waiting in line to see
three minutes of something

03:17.948 --> 03:21.283
the rest of the world will have
to wait two weeks to see.

03:21.285 --> 03:22.784
Now, don't you feel silly?

03:22.786 --> 03:25.386
We're not going to Comic-Con.

03:25.388 --> 03:28.423
Donna, let me talk
to you for a second.

03:29.592 --> 03:31.326
[MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

03:35.864 --> 03:38.133
[WHIMPERING INDISTINCTLY]

03:43.806 --> 03:45.840
[SOBBING]

03:51.814 --> 03:54.516
Looks like we're going
to San Diego.

03:54.518 --> 03:56.918
I'm ready.

03:56.920 --> 03:58.669
[♪]

04:10.082 --> 04:12.483
Yeah, this all seems very
necessary.

04:12.485 --> 04:14.752
Aren't there two wars
going on right now?

04:14.754 --> 04:17.755
Come on, Rallo, this is
what they're fighting for.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.191
Well, now I'm not sure
who I want to win.

04:20.193 --> 04:22.761
Ha-ha. This <i>Cleveland Show</i>
not too bad.

04:22.763 --> 04:24.996
Move over, <i>King of Hill.</i>

04:26.182 --> 04:27.348
What's going on here?

04:27.350 --> 04:30.184
Kevin Smith and Harry Knowles
are fighting over a corndog.

04:30.186 --> 04:32.654
[♪]

04:32.656 --> 04:34.072
[GROWLS]

04:44.534 --> 04:45.817
[BOTH GRUNTING]

04:47.720 --> 04:49.788
Join us, Zach Galifianakis,

04:49.790 --> 04:52.624
and together we can rule
the galaxy.

04:52.626 --> 04:55.393
[LAUGHING MENACINGLY]

04:55.395 --> 04:57.128
Hm.
[SQUEALS]

04:57.130 --> 05:00.665
Oh, Donna, once these mouth
breathers see <i>Waderman,</i>

05:00.667 --> 05:03.234
my life is gonna change forever.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.236
I'm gonna go set up my booth.

05:05.238 --> 05:06.538
And I'm gonna go stand in line

05:06.540 --> 05:10.275
for an autograph
from Scott Bakula.

05:10.277 --> 05:12.810
[LAUGHING]

05:19.652 --> 05:22.404
Oh, God, no!

05:22.406 --> 05:25.006
Mom, that's you!
Damn!

05:26.359 --> 05:28.376
Damn.

05:30.629 --> 05:32.397
[♪]

05:35.801 --> 05:37.803
Sure, but I get grounded,

05:37.805 --> 05:41.456
when I take my school photo
in a mink coat and underwear.

05:41.458 --> 05:44.426
Rallo, I did that a long time
ago and it was a mistake.

05:44.428 --> 05:47.462
Things you do on camera
can come back to haunt you.

05:47.464 --> 05:48.797
I gotta call Federline.

05:48.799 --> 05:50.131
Listen to me, Rallo.

05:50.133 --> 05:52.534
No one can know
about that screening.

05:52.536 --> 05:54.569
Especially Cleveland.

05:54.571 --> 05:55.503
Mm-hm.

05:55.505 --> 05:57.972
And that's where
it gets tricky for you.

05:57.974 --> 06:00.842
I'll keep my mouth shut,
but it ain't gonna be cheap.

06:00.844 --> 06:03.578
Four dollars.
Fine.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.179
Now, go find Cleveland.

06:05.181 --> 06:08.066
I'm going to get
that screening cancelled.

06:08.068 --> 06:11.402
So apparently, she's not worried
about her 5-year-old boy

06:11.404 --> 06:15.206
alone in a convention center
full of grown men in costumes.

06:15.208 --> 06:17.375
All right, then.

06:22.798 --> 06:26.018
Weirdo. Hey, Rallo,
I need an attention getter

06:26.020 --> 06:28.153
and since I can't afford
a hot Asian girl

06:28.155 --> 06:29.321
to dress up like a cat,

06:29.323 --> 06:30.622
and stand in front of my booth,

06:30.624 --> 06:32.857
why don't you help me out
and be my Squirt?

06:32.859 --> 06:35.410
Squirt is Waderman's sidekick.
All right.

06:35.412 --> 06:37.812
But it's gonna cost you.
How much?

06:37.814 --> 06:39.564
What's the number after four?

06:39.566 --> 06:42.767
Five.
Five dollars.

06:42.769 --> 06:45.470
I got 45 dollars.

06:47.073 --> 06:51.059
Hey! Harry Pockmarks, you look
like you could use a hero.

06:51.061 --> 06:54.246
How about you, fat Spider-Woman?

06:55.698 --> 06:57.481
[HIP-HOP PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

07:06.192 --> 07:10.161
Hello, Comic-Con.
I am Katee Sackhoff.

07:10.163 --> 07:12.797
Or am I Eliza Dushku?

07:12.799 --> 07:16.968
Nope.
I'm Emily Deschanel from <i>Bones.</i>

07:16.970 --> 07:18.853
[CHEERING]

07:25.661 --> 07:28.596
I just think <i>Firefly</i>
was totally overrated.

07:28.598 --> 07:29.630
[ALL GASP]

07:29.632 --> 07:31.365
I kind of agree.

07:31.367 --> 07:34.419
I mean, you can't have
a whole ship of Han Solos.

07:34.421 --> 07:38.590
If everyone is Han Solo,
then no one is Han Solo.

07:38.592 --> 07:40.691
Oh, yeah. That's true.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

07:42.094 --> 07:43.811
What is this?

07:43.813 --> 07:45.880
ANNOUNCER:
<i>This fall on NBC</i>

07:45.882 --> 07:48.566
<i>we're forcing</i>
<i>David Schwimmer to return</i>

07:48.568 --> 07:51.403
<i>to network TV</i>
<i>in a new hit comedy.</i>

07:51.405 --> 07:53.037
Yay.

07:53.039 --> 07:56.624
<i>See what happens when one of</i>
<i>America's favorite</i> Friends,

07:56.626 --> 08:01.095
<i>becomes Kalamazoo's</i>
<i>least favorite swimming coach.</i>

08:01.097 --> 08:04.331
I'm here against my will.

08:04.333 --> 08:05.717
<i>Schwim Team.</i>

08:05.719 --> 08:08.520
<i>Coming this fall to NBC.</i>

08:08.522 --> 08:11.072
<i>Don't worry, we're almost done.</i>

08:11.074 --> 08:13.492
That doesn't have anything
to do with Comic-Con.

08:13.494 --> 08:15.226
Why is it even here?

08:15.228 --> 08:17.896
You guys talking about Schwim?
Gonna get some Schwim this fall?

08:17.898 --> 08:20.748
Schwim? Here, have a T-shirt.

08:23.385 --> 08:26.754
The <i>Doctor Horrible Sing-a-long</i>
is now full.

08:26.756 --> 08:29.790
No one else will
be allowed inside.

08:29.792 --> 08:32.627
What? But we've been waiting
all morning.

08:32.629 --> 08:34.629
Sorry.
They're from Hollywood,

08:34.631 --> 08:36.598
so they're more important
than you.

08:36.600 --> 08:40.585
Well, I guess I could wait in
line to boo M. Night Shyamalan.

08:40.587 --> 08:42.153
Frak this!

08:42.155 --> 08:44.456
Comic-Con belongs to us.

08:44.458 --> 08:46.775
It's bad enough
those <i>Twilight</i> fruit blades

08:46.777 --> 08:48.042
think they belong here,

08:48.044 --> 08:51.212
but that other Hollywood
crap is inexcusable.

08:51.214 --> 08:53.314
You're right.
We have to fight back.

08:53.316 --> 08:56.785
By posting sarcastic barbs
on message boards.

08:56.787 --> 08:59.271
No. I mean, really fight back.

08:59.273 --> 09:01.373
This is our house,

09:01.375 --> 09:03.691
and it's time
we take back Comic-Con.

09:03.693 --> 09:05.126
[CHEERING]

09:05.128 --> 09:07.262
We have room for one more.

09:07.264 --> 09:10.782
Screw you guys.

09:10.784 --> 09:14.068
An aquatic superhero
who lacks the ability to swim.

09:14.070 --> 09:17.471
Apparently, he also has a
superhuman tolerance for irony,

09:17.473 --> 09:20.892
which, unfortunately, I do not.

09:20.894 --> 09:25.347
Worst. Cameo. Ever.

09:31.103 --> 09:33.505
[PLAYING FLAMENCO MUSIC]

09:33.507 --> 09:35.806
Are you Robert Rodriguez?

09:35.808 --> 09:40.478
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

09:40.480 --> 09:41.746
You're Cocoa Bang Bang.

09:41.748 --> 09:45.016
I've been in love with you
since I first saw your movie.

09:45.018 --> 09:47.752
Nice rack.
Don't try and sweet-talk me.

09:47.754 --> 09:49.854
Look, I am here
this weekend to support

09:49.856 --> 09:51.021
my husband's comic book,

09:51.023 --> 09:52.957
<i>Waffleman</i> or something,

09:52.959 --> 09:55.109
not to be embarrassed
by some stupid movie

09:55.111 --> 09:56.244
I should never have made.

09:56.246 --> 09:58.479
Stupid movie?
<i>Hot Cocoa Bang Bang</i>

09:58.481 --> 10:00.148
inspired me to make
<i>El Mariachi.</i>

10:00.150 --> 10:02.183
And for a whole year
I greeted my friends with,

10:02.185 --> 10:04.152
"You going back
in the trunk, bitch."

10:04.154 --> 10:05.619
Come to the screening.

10:05.621 --> 10:08.139
If you want you can even wear
your original costume.

10:08.141 --> 10:10.408
I occasionally make
my girlfriend sleep in it.

10:10.410 --> 10:11.860
Listen to me.

10:11.862 --> 10:15.129
That screening
is not going to happen.

10:15.131 --> 10:16.731
Look, I don't want you
to be upset,

10:16.733 --> 10:18.366
so if that's how you feel, fine.

10:18.368 --> 10:20.635
No screening.
It was an honor to meet you.

10:20.637 --> 10:23.905
Thank you.
It was nice meeting you too.

10:23.907 --> 10:27.842
Your skin is even moister
than Antonio Banderas'.

10:27.844 --> 10:29.661
Speak English.

10:29.663 --> 10:32.997
Nerds, hear me!

10:32.999 --> 10:35.950
Comic-Con is not a place
for David Schwimmer,

10:35.952 --> 10:39.854
and his bad-even-for-NBC sitcom.

10:39.856 --> 10:43.607
It's a place where people like
us can be ourselves,

10:43.609 --> 10:46.478
and not worry about getting
pushed around by bullies,

10:46.480 --> 10:48.379
or talking to girls.

10:48.381 --> 10:51.148
I'm a girl.
My name's Rebecca.

10:51.150 --> 10:53.034
You are now my girlfriend.

10:53.036 --> 10:54.903
No butt stuff.

10:56.404 --> 10:58.239
We have many different beliefs,

10:58.241 --> 11:01.475
but today we must put them aside
and unite.

11:01.477 --> 11:03.011
Gryffindor and Slytherin.

11:04.846 --> 11:06.998
Jedi and Sith.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.734
Jack Nicholson Joker
and Heath Ledger Joker.

11:09.736 --> 11:13.538
This is our time
to take what's ours,

11:13.540 --> 11:18.275
for tonight we dine in hell!

11:18.277 --> 11:20.011
[CHEERING]

11:21.613 --> 11:24.315
Donna, you'll never guess
what happened.

11:24.317 --> 11:26.016
Someone bought <i>Waderman</i>

11:26.018 --> 11:28.219
and wants to make
it into a movie.

11:28.221 --> 11:29.436
That seems unlikely.

11:29.438 --> 11:31.272
Who bought it?
I did.

11:31.274 --> 11:32.990
Mm.

11:32.992 --> 11:35.827
Donna, I'd like you to meet
Robert Rodriguez,

11:35.829 --> 11:39.029
America's greatest
Mexican film director.

11:39.031 --> 11:41.733
Actually, I was born in Texas.

11:41.735 --> 11:46.320
Oh. He's one of America's
top 75 film directors.

11:46.322 --> 11:49.356
Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you too.

11:49.358 --> 11:50.625
I was telling Cleveland

11:50.627 --> 11:52.594
I think <i>Walrusman</i>
could be a huge movie.

11:52.596 --> 11:55.063
Did you hear that, Donna?
Huge.

11:55.065 --> 11:57.665
It's <i>Waderman,</i> by the way.
Of course.

11:57.667 --> 11:59.567
But if this movie
is going to be accurate,

11:59.569 --> 12:01.602
I need to know
Waderman's limits.

12:01.604 --> 12:03.304
Why don't you go to the ocean,

12:03.306 --> 12:04.505
and see how long you can stand

12:04.507 --> 12:06.106
in shallow water
before you cramp up.

12:06.108 --> 12:07.608
You got it.

12:07.610 --> 12:10.678
Rallo, pack it up,
we're going to the beach.

12:10.680 --> 12:11.996
This town has a beach?

12:11.998 --> 12:14.198
Then why is everyone
in here so pale?

12:14.200 --> 12:16.417
What the hell do you think
you're doing?

12:16.419 --> 12:19.186
Donna, <i>Hot Cocoa Bang Bang</i>
is important to me.

12:19.188 --> 12:21.689
I own the only remaining copy,
and after tonight,

12:21.691 --> 12:24.391
I promise I'll never show it
to another living person.

12:24.393 --> 12:27.228
Just come to the screening.
And what if I say no?

12:27.230 --> 12:29.030
Look how happy he is.

12:29.032 --> 12:30.314
[HUMMING]

12:30.316 --> 12:33.017
It'd be a shame if I had
to take that away from him.

12:33.019 --> 12:35.219
So you think by making
my husband's dream come true,

12:35.221 --> 12:36.587
I'll do what you want?

12:36.589 --> 12:37.839
You're not the only person here

12:37.841 --> 12:39.340
who would buy Cleveland's comic.

12:39.342 --> 12:41.609
Have you read it? Ahem.

12:41.611 --> 12:43.678
"And Waderman was all,
'Boom, boom.'

12:43.680 --> 12:47.147
And the bad guys were all,
'Vroom, vroom,' in their cars."

12:47.149 --> 12:51.318
All right, I'll be there.
Super.

12:51.320 --> 12:53.221
[PLAYING FLAMENCO MUSIC]

12:55.991 --> 12:58.810
I should not be turned
on right now.

13:01.663 --> 13:02.730
Oh. There's a cramp.

13:02.732 --> 13:05.266
Four hours and 47 minutes.

13:05.268 --> 13:07.568
That's good. Or bad.

13:07.570 --> 13:09.270
I don't know what
the average is.

13:09.272 --> 13:11.572
I don't know what
we're doing out here.

13:11.574 --> 13:13.991
We must tell Robert Rodriguez.
Come, Squirt.

13:13.993 --> 13:15.460
You go on ahead.

13:15.462 --> 13:18.663
I'm thinking about giving
my sand castle a guest house.

13:18.665 --> 13:20.698
Maybe a little fold-out bed.

13:20.700 --> 13:23.501
Mother-in-law comes to visit,
no problem.

13:23.503 --> 13:25.636
Maybe a bay window.

13:25.638 --> 13:29.307
Sit up there, read a book. Yeah.

13:29.309 --> 13:32.343
I would kill
for a beer right now.

13:41.537 --> 13:42.853
[GUN COCKS]

13:42.855 --> 13:45.773
<i>Bang, bang, honkeys!</i>

13:45.775 --> 13:48.076
[GRUNTING]

13:48.078 --> 13:49.260
[CHEERING]

13:49.262 --> 13:50.594
You're a star, Donna.

13:50.596 --> 13:52.363
They love you.

14:00.555 --> 14:02.740
[GASPS]
[AUDIENCE CHEERING]

14:02.742 --> 14:04.058
Donna?

14:04.060 --> 14:05.826
Cleveland!

14:05.828 --> 14:07.812
What the hell's going on here?

14:07.814 --> 14:09.380
Shh. If you have a question,

14:09.382 --> 14:10.715
you can stand
in line and wait

14:10.717 --> 14:12.517
for the Q & A
like everyone else.

14:12.519 --> 14:14.018
Ugh. Fine.

14:15.971 --> 14:17.171
Hi, Robert.

14:17.173 --> 14:20.208
I'm also a filmmaker
and writer/producer,

14:20.210 --> 14:22.143
and sometimes actor.

14:22.145 --> 14:23.811
I also have a band.

14:23.813 --> 14:25.429
Oh.

14:25.431 --> 14:27.865
Um, two years ago
I sent you a script.

14:27.867 --> 14:29.567
It was called <i>Mexicannibals.</i>

14:29.569 --> 14:32.570
Never read it.
Thank you.

14:32.572 --> 14:35.156
Yes?
First of all, big fan.

14:35.158 --> 14:37.258
I've got a comment
and a question.

14:37.260 --> 14:39.627
The comment: Donna!

14:39.629 --> 14:42.730
Now my question: Why?

14:44.816 --> 14:47.485
[♪]

14:47.487 --> 14:49.304
Cleveland, I am so sorry.

14:49.306 --> 14:50.704
And I'd be so embarrassed

14:50.706 --> 14:52.840
if anyone back home
found out about this.

14:52.842 --> 14:54.959
Oh, please, Donna,
you were arrested

14:54.961 --> 14:57.094
at the dog track four days ago.

14:57.096 --> 14:58.545
She hit me first, Cleveland.

14:58.547 --> 15:00.214
[SIGHS]

15:00.216 --> 15:02.567
Robert Rodriguez promised
that if I came to the screening,

15:02.569 --> 15:05.436
he'd never show that movie
to another living person.

15:05.438 --> 15:07.521
Are you kidding?
You heard that crowd.

15:07.523 --> 15:09.723
